---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Scoring — Awesome WWM Base Building"
  description="How guild base scores are calculated in the Awesome WWM Base Building showcase."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-10">
    <div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-1">⭐ Scoring</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">
        How guild bases are ranked in the showcase.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">How it works</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Each guild base has a thread in our Discord forum. Community members can vote by
        reacting to the thread's first post. Reactions are tallied automatically twice a day
        and converted into a score.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl ring-1 ring-border">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-border bg-muted/40 text-muted-foreground text-left">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Reaction</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-lg">⭐</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-semibold">+2</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted-foreground">Strong appreciation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-lg">👍</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-semibold">+1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted-foreground">General vote</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-lg">🔥</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-semibold">+1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted-foreground">Hype vote</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Voter weight</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        To keep rankings fair, votes from community members who engage with many guilds count
        more. A voter who has reacted to at least 5 different guild threads carries a higher
        weight than someone who only reacted to one.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        This prevents guild leaders from inflating their own score by asking members to vote
        only for them.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Roles</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Reaching score thresholds unlocks Discord roles:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-base">🏗️</span>
          <span><strong>Base Builder</strong> — awarded when your guild base passes the minimum score threshold</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-base">🗳️</span>
          <span><strong>Base Critic</strong> — awarded to active community voters who engage across many guilds</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-xl bg-muted/40 ring-1 ring-border px-6 py-5">
      <p class="text-sm">
        Questions about your score?{" "}
        <a href="https://discord.gg/Qygt9u26Bn" class="underline hover:text-foreground transition-colors">
          Ask in the Discord server.
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
